HEADWORD: Dissertation
<hw>Dis`ser*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dissertatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>dissertation</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
formal or elaborate argumentative discourse, oral or written; a
disquisition; an essay; a discussion; <as>as, <ex>Dissertations</ex> on
the Prophecies</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dissertational</ent>⟦br⟧
